==English==
===Etymology===
From Old and modern French ''exemption'', or from Latin ''[[exemptio]]'', from ''[[eximere]]''

===Noun===
'''exemption'''
# An act of [[exempt]]ing.
# The state of being [[exempt]]; [[immunity]].
# A [[deduction]] from the normal amount of [[tax]]es.
# [[Freedom]] from a [[defect]] or [[weakness]].

